That=E2=80=99s the opportunity that we have. It=E2=80=99s in some sense end=
less, but we also have responsibility. We have the responsibility to ensure=
 that these technologies are empowering everyone, these technologies are cr=
eating equitable growth by ensuring that every industry is able to grow and=
 create employment. But we also have a responsibility as a tech industry to=
 build trust in technology.

In fact Hans Jonas was a philosopher who worked in the 50s, 60s, and he wro=
te a paper on technology and responsibility=E2=80=A6he talks about act so t=
hat the effects of your action are compatible with permanence or genuine li=
fe. That=E2=80=99s something that we need to reflect on, because he was tal=
king about the power of technology being such that it far outstrips our abi=
